                <note rend="inline" type="source">767.68/319: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-09-14T12:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 14, 1922—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 5:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>181. Wireless just received from my chief of staff at Smyrna states city is
                    burning and that all American naturalized citizens and that women of native born
                    Americans have been evacuated to Athens on destroyer <hi rend="italic"
                        >Simpson</hi> in charge of Consul Horton. No details are given.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
